oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Psittacosis Update
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clipsham, Robert C.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: In an effort to bring to light the current thinking on an age old problem, I have combined a number of aspects concerning the disease known as psittacosis, or more commonly referred to as parrot fever. This has been a traditional subject for aviculturists and avian practitioners, not only as a disease requiring treatment in birds, but also as a tremendous diagnostic challenge at times, a fearful social subject among breeders and brokers, a legal issue and as a human health...
